00:15:40,407 --> 00:15:43,007
- We have a real problem.

291
00:15:43,009 --> 00:15:44,339
- Is it in the box?

292
00:15:45,812 --> 00:15:47,812
- Professor Sunderland
came looking for a book

293
00:15:47,814 --> 00:15:49,954
from the Physical
Cottage Library,

294
00:15:49,955 --> 00:15:51,680
and it's missing.

295
00:15:51,685 --> 00:15:52,945
I diverted her attention, but...

296
00:15:52,953 --> 00:15:54,323
- What does that
have to do with the box?

297
00:15:54,324 --> 00:15:56,588
- Books at Brakebills, Quentin,

298
00:15:56,589 --> 00:15:57,789
are not just books.

299
00:15:57,791 --> 00:15:59,160
One goes missing, it's not just

300
00:15:59,161 --> 00:16:00,928
a library fine
we're talking about here.

301
00:16:00,929 --> 00:16:03,357
- What're we talking about?
- We're talking about...

302
00:16:03,363 --> 00:16:05,831
We have...

303
00:16:05,832 --> 00:16:07,632
occasional parties.

304
00:16:07,634 --> 00:16:09,334
During one, someone took a book,

305
00:16:09,336 --> 00:16:11,036
and if we don't find that book

306
00:16:11,037 --> 00:16:13,137
the faculty are going to take
a harder look at our parties,

307
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:14,909
and that cannot happen, Quentin.

308
00:16:17,577 --> 00:16:20,507
- So you gonna tell me
what's in the box or...

309
00:16:24,851 --> 00:16:26,719
What the hell is that?

310
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:28,350
- The missing book
is Volume One.

311
00:16:28,355 --> 00:16:31,915
That... is Volume Two.

312
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:37,496
She's going to lead us
to her mate.

313
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:39,357
- Oh.

314
00:16:39,366 --> 00:16:42,096
<i>- Odemknout.</i>

315
00:16:45,171 --> 00:16:47,171
<i>Odemknout.</i>

316
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:48,640
Shit.

317
00:16:48,641 --> 00:16:50,541
Uh, let me...
Let me try it again.

318
00:16:50,543 --> 00:16:53,479
- Should be easy.
- You're distracted.

319
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,410
I know I have a lot going on.

320
00:16:55,415 --> 00:16:56,845
- No, you don't.
- You have this spell.

321
00:16:56,850 --> 00:16:58,520
That's it.

322
00:17:00,487 --> 00:17:03,687
- So how do you manage it all?

323
00:17:03,690 --> 00:17:06,859
Juggling magic and your life?

324
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:11,160
- I don't understand
the question.

325
00:17:11,164 --> 00:17:12,898
I'm not judging you.

326
00:17:12,899 --> 00:17:16,429
I started out like you
and you have a good life.

327
00:17:16,436 --> 00:17:18,336
Boyfriend.

328
00:17:18,338 --> 00:17:20,538
Probably think
he keeps you centered.

329
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:22,608
- Right?
- Kinda.

330
00:17:22,609 --> 00:17:26,578
- Or, you know, you're keeping
him around in case you fail here

331
00:17:26,579 --> 00:17:29,379
and need to fall back.

332
00:17:29,382 --> 00:17:32,251
All I know...
you have to mean it

333
00:17:32,252 --> 00:17:33,682
for magic to work.

334
00:17:33,686 --> 00:17:37,356
Something clicks
when you're all-in,

335
00:17:37,357 --> 00:17:42,057
and the real big stuff,
you can't do it

336
00:17:42,062 --> 00:17:45,302
till you're doing it
without a net.

337
00:17:58,211 --> 00:18:00,946
- I...

338
00:18:00,947 --> 00:18:02,377
I need your help.

339
00:18:02,382 --> 00:18:05,622
- That wasn't so hard, was it?

340
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:09,150
- Look, I'm just trying

341
00:18:09,155 --> 00:18:11,115
to find out what happened
to my brother.

342
00:18:11,124 --> 00:18:13,624
He was a student here
five years ago.

343
00:18:13,626 --> 00:18:15,486
- Okay.

344
00:18:18,565 --> 00:18:20,765
- He was a physical kid.

345
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:23,327
His name was Charlie,

346
00:18:23,336 --> 00:18:24,766
and he died.

347
00:18:24,771 --> 00:18:28,740
- Know what?
- I did hear about that.

348
00:18:28,741 --> 00:18:30,909
At Woof, right?

349
00:18:30,910 --> 00:18:34,279
Five, six years back?

350
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:36,080
It's all making sense now.

351
00:18:36,082 --> 00:18:38,250
- What is?
- You.

352
00:18:38,251 --> 00:18:40,081
The awkward thing.

353
00:18:40,086 --> 00:18:43,316
The anger underneath
the ineffable air of tragedy

354
00:18:43,323 --> 00:18:45,993
you wear like a perfume.

355
00:18:47,827 --> 00:18:50,857
- Look, can you just tell me
what you know about Charlie?

356
00:18:50,864 --> 00:18:52,934
- Please?
- Loathe as I am to admit it,

357
00:18:52,935 --> 00:18:56,702
I don't actually know anything.

358
00:18:56,703 --> 00:18:58,770
Although, there was a girl

359
00:18:58,771 --> 00:19:01,306
from Charlie's year who might.

360
00:19:01,307 --> 00:19:03,837
Emily Greenstreet.

361
00:19:03,843 --> 00:19:05,310
- Who was she?

362
00:19:05,311 --> 00:19:06,778
- Just a girl.

363
00:19:06,779 --> 00:19:09,448
When he died,
apparently she took it hard.

364
00:19:09,449 --> 00:19:11,379
Dropped out.
Gave up magic.

365
00:19:11,384 --> 00:19:12,951
The Full Muggle.

366
00:19:12,952 --> 00:19:14,820
It was a bit of a scandal.

367
00:19:14,821 --> 00:19:16,221
- Where is she now?

368
00:19:16,222 --> 00:19:17,456
- The city.

369
00:19:17,457 --> 00:19:19,017
Fogg set her up with a job

370
00:19:19,025 --> 00:19:22,355
which is how you know
they're hiding something big.

371
00:19:22,362 --> 00:19:24,562
I know how to find her.

372
00:19:24,564 --> 00:19:26,004
Come on, I'll show you.

373
00:19:26,005 --> 00:19:28,467
- I'd actually
prefer to go alone.

374
00:19:28,468 --> 00:19:31,737
- Oh, I know you would, but...

375
00:19:31,738 --> 00:19:33,838
what choice do you really have?

376
00:19:44,684 --> 00:19:47,152
- Penny.

377
00:19:47,153 --> 00:19:50,556
Welcome.
Knew you were coming.

378
00:19:50,557 --> 00:19:52,257
I know you've been
dreading this,

379
00:19:52,258 --> 00:19:54,588
but you're gonna like it.

380
00:19:54,594 --> 00:19:57,829
The coves are for meditation

381
00:19:57,830 --> 00:20:00,530
while the enclosed
"Consciousness Areas"

382
00:20:00,533 --> 00:20:04,103
are reserved as a place
to cry, and process.

383
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:08,540
Hm.

384
00:20:08,541 --> 00:20:10,876
We call it "The Amplifier."

385
00:20:10,877 --> 00:20:13,007
So basically, it's like turning

386
00:20:13,012 --> 00:20:15,112
your psychic powers up to 11.

387
00:20:15,114 --> 00:20:16,754
- Why would you wanna do that?

388
00:20:16,755 --> 00:20:18,417
- Oh, I get it.

389
00:20:18,418 --> 00:20:20,848
You're one of those guys
who's trying to shut it out.

390
00:20:20,853 --> 00:20:23,053
You wanna get control of it

391
00:20:23,056 --> 00:20:26,586
or it will mess up your shit
big time,

392
00:20:26,593 --> 00:20:28,563
and this is the best place
to practice.

393
00:20:28,564 --> 00:20:31,129
- So...

394
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:32,360
I do what?

395
00:20:32,365 --> 00:20:33,555
- Sit.

396
00:20:33,566 --> 00:20:34,866
Relax.

397
00:20:34,867 --> 00:20:36,567
Let your mind wander.

398
00:20:36,569 --> 00:20:37,936
It's pretty simple.

399
00:20:37,937 --> 00:20:40,297
But you gotta start
by letting go, tough guy.

400
00:20:40,306 --> 00:20:43,136
Less talking.

401
00:20:43,142 --> 00:20:44,412
No touching.

402
00:21:12,272 --> 00:21:14,006
<i>- Help!</i>

403
00:21:14,007 --> 00:21:16,507
<i>Please!
Help me!</i>

404
00:21:26,352 --> 00:21:28,052
- Emily?

405
00:21:29,455 --> 00:21:30,815
No, don't run.

406
00:21:30,823 --> 00:21:32,493
These shoes are insane.

407
00:21:35,528 --> 00:21:38,828
- You're from Brakebills,
aren't you?

408
00:21:38,831 --> 00:21:40,231
That part of my life
is behind me.

409
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:43,073
- I'm sorry.
- Charlie was my brother.

410
00:21:49,575 --> 00:21:53,205
I just wanna know
what happened to him.

411
00:21:53,212 --> 00:21:56,648
- Your brother saved my life.

412
00:21:56,649 --> 00:21:59,879
Well, he tried to at least.

413
00:21:59,886 --> 00:22:03,016
So, I fell for this professor.

414
00:22:03,022 --> 00:22:05,390
I know how it sounds,

415
00:22:05,391 --> 00:22:08,391
but I was young and...

416
00:22:08,394 --> 00:22:11,363
and he loved me.

417
00:22:11,364 --> 00:22:15,267
But then, well, he was married.

418
00:22:15,268 --> 00:22:17,368
You know how it is
when you're that age.

419
00:22:17,370 --> 00:22:20,770
You get... terrible ideas.

420
00:22:20,773 --> 00:22:23,342
- Hmm.

421
00:22:23,343 --> 00:22:25,610
Like what?

422
00:22:25,611 --> 00:22:29,411
- I thought I could
make him love me again.

423
00:22:29,415 --> 00:22:31,575
- Oh, some kind of love spell?

424
00:22:31,584 --> 00:22:34,753
- No.

425
00:22:34,754 --> 00:22:36,621
No.

426
00:22:36,622 --> 00:22:41,526
I thought if I could
make myself prettier.

427
00:22:41,527 --> 00:22:44,127
- Oh... God.

428
00:22:44,130 --> 00:22:46,430
- No one warned you
how dangerous that was?

429
00:22:46,432 --> 00:22:49,368
- I knew,
but I'd convinced myself

430
00:22:49,369 --> 00:22:54,039
that it was the only way.

431
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:56,908
It took me weeks

432
00:22:56,909 --> 00:22:59,709
to figure out how to do it,

433
00:22:59,712 --> 00:23:02,412
and...

434
00:23:02,415 --> 00:23:04,875
<i>when I did, well, you...</i>

435
00:23:04,884 --> 00:23:06,624
<i>You can imagine how that went.</i>

436
00:23:14,394 --> 00:23:17,094
No...

437
00:23:24,704 --> 00:23:28,273
I was gonna... I was
gonna kill myself.

438
00:23:28,274 --> 00:23:31,076
Emily!

439
00:23:31,077 --> 00:23:33,237
Wait!

440
00:23:33,246 --> 00:23:35,476
What happened?

441
00:23:35,481 --> 00:23:37,481
What did you do?

442
00:23:42,688 --> 00:23:44,956
- Please.

443
00:23:44,957 --> 00:23:47,787
I just wanna help.

444
00:23:59,138 --> 00:24:01,938
- Don't tell anyone, please.

445
00:24:01,941 --> 00:24:03,271
- Course not.

446
00:24:03,276 --> 00:24:04,876
Wait here.
I'll be back.

447
00:24:04,877 --> 00:24:06,507
I'm gonna fix this.

448
00:24:09,849 --> 00:24:12,717
He mashed a...

449
00:24:12,718 --> 00:24:14,148
bunch of stuff together.

450
00:24:14,153 --> 00:24:15,987
<i>It was...</i>

451
00:24:15,988 --> 00:24:17,558
<i>It was totally untested.</i>

452
00:24:19,492 --> 00:24:21,860
I really believed

453
00:24:21,861 --> 00:24:25,030
he might actually
be able to undo what I did.

454
00:24:25,031 --> 00:24:28,131
He was a good magician.

455
00:24:28,134 --> 00:24:30,368
You know, he...

456
00:24:30,369 --> 00:24:34,406
He woulda done anything for me.

457
00:24:34,407 --> 00:24:36,507
<i>It was a lot.
It was... it was...</i>

458
00:24:36,509 --> 00:24:39,539
It was too much.

459
00:24:39,545 --> 00:24:43,575
I begged him to stop,
but he wouldn't,

460
00:24:43,583 --> 00:24:47,053
and that's when it went
totally out of control.

461
00:24:57,396 --> 00:24:59,756
It burned...

462
00:24:59,765 --> 00:25:02,995
right through him...

463
00:25:03,002 --> 00:25:07,506
until he wasn't there anymore.

464
00:25:07,507 --> 00:25:11,007
He was...
Do you know what a Niffin is?

465
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:15,210
- No.
- Yes.

466
00:25:15,214 --> 00:25:17,184
- It's when too much
runs through you.

467
00:25:17,185 --> 00:25:19,417
Consumes you.

468
00:25:19,418 --> 00:25:22,448
Only the magic is left,

469
00:25:22,455 --> 00:25:25,385
but you're not

470
00:25:25,391 --> 00:25:26,621
you anymore.

471
00:25:26,626 --> 00:25:28,956
You're...

472
00:25:28,961 --> 00:25:31,930
lost.

473
00:25:31,931 --> 00:25:34,399
- Where did Charlie go?

474
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,867
- I don't know.

475
00:25:35,868 --> 00:25:39,868
He was just gone.

476
00:25:39,872 --> 00:25:42,272
I never saw him again.

477
00:25:42,275 --> 00:25:45,075
- Um, who did all this then?

478
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:49,480
- My professor.

479
00:25:49,482 --> 00:25:52,751
- Well, I guess you got
his attention after all.

480
00:25:52,752 --> 00:25:54,152
- I quit school.

481
00:25:54,153 --> 00:25:56,721
Gave up magic,
and never looked back.

482
00:25:56,722 --> 00:26:01,362
I'm so sorry about Charlie.

