00:26:05,731 --> 00:26:09,131
- Hear that?
- She's getting excited.

484
00:26:09,135 --> 00:26:11,435
I think we're close.

485
00:26:11,437 --> 00:26:13,867
Hold this, will you?

486
00:26:17,777 --> 00:26:21,807
This bodega is warded
up the ass.

487
00:26:25,451 --> 00:26:26,781
Hedge witches.

488
00:26:26,786 --> 00:26:29,486
Amateurs.
Magical D-leaguers.

489
00:26:29,488 --> 00:26:31,818
Sad and desperate people.

490
00:26:31,824 --> 00:26:34,764
Once one of 'em offered
to blow me for a spell.

491
00:26:34,765 --> 00:26:37,260
It was fairly worth it.

492
00:26:37,263 --> 00:26:38,663
Let me do the talking.

493
00:27:02,955 --> 00:27:04,185
- These are witches?

494
00:27:04,190 --> 00:27:06,558
- Hm. Pathetic. No?

495
00:27:06,559 --> 00:27:10,528
Ugh, this kid's trying
Popper number four.

496
00:27:10,529 --> 00:27:12,759
It's painful.

