and we want our book.

506
00:27:40,926 --> 00:27:43,756
- We don't have
your stupid book.

507
00:27:55,107 --> 00:27:57,007
Are they?

508
00:27:58,310 --> 00:27:59,778
- Yep.

509
00:27:59,779 --> 00:28:01,079
Love wins.

510
00:28:15,194 --> 00:28:16,728
- Hey!

511
00:28:16,729 --> 00:28:18,059
So, that's it?

512
00:28:18,064 --> 00:28:19,334
That's all you're
gonna say to me?

513
00:28:19,335 --> 00:28:21,031
- Don't talk to her.
- Keep going.

514
00:28:21,033 --> 00:28:23,133
- I don't know what
you're doing here, Jules.

515
00:28:23,135 --> 00:28:24,965
You're better than this.

516
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:26,738
- You say that
like I had a choice.

517
00:28:26,739 --> 00:28:28,209
- Of course you have a choice.
- No, because guess what?

518
00:28:28,210 --> 00:28:31,076
Magic wasn't just handed to me.

519
00:28:31,077 --> 00:28:35,207
I told you to please
tell them about me.

520
00:28:35,214 --> 00:28:37,014
At first, you know,
I thought maybe

521
00:28:37,016 --> 00:28:39,146
they'd actually test me again,

522
00:28:39,151 --> 00:28:40,821
and then I figured someone
would at least come

523
00:28:40,822 --> 00:28:43,850
and try to take my memory
again, and then...

524
00:28:43,856 --> 00:28:46,556
just waiting.

525
00:28:46,559 --> 00:28:48,029
It took me weeks to realize

526
00:28:48,030 --> 00:28:51,996
you never even
told them about me at all.

527
00:28:51,997 --> 00:28:54,766
- Look, Jules, I...
- You were my best friend.

